# TaxBackwards.ca — Cursor Project Rules

## Project Overview
TaxBackwards.ca is a Canadian reverse sales tax calculator for bookkeepers, freelancers, sole proprietors, and small business owners. Users enter a gross transaction total, select a province, and receive a net consideration base and claimable Input Tax Credit (ITC) amount. All calculations run entirely client-side with no backend, no API calls, and no external dependencies.

## Tech Stack
- Vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript only
- No frameworks, no libraries, no npm packages in the frontend
- Node.js and npm used only for the backend scraper and test suite
- Hosted on Cloudflare Pages via GitHub repository
- Analytics via Cloudflare Web Analytics or Plausible script tag only

## Core Coding Rules
- Never introduce frontend frameworks or dependencies under any circumstances
- Never use React, Vue, Angular, jQuery, or any other frontend library
- Never use innerHTML to render user input or calculation outputs — always use textContent to prevent XSS vulnerabilities
- Never use eval() anywhere in the codebase
- Prefer simple readable code over clever solutions
- No build steps, no bundlers, no webpack, no vite in the frontend
- No package.json dependencies for the frontend — the frontend is pure static files only
- Every function must do one thing and be named to describe that thing
- All code must be written to be understandable by a developer with limited experience

## Critical Math Rules — Non-Negotiable
- Never use native JavaScript floating point arithmetic directly on currency values — floating point errors corrupt accounting calculations
- All currency inputs must be immediately converted to integers by scaling: Math.round(value * 10000)
- All calculations must be performed on scaled integers only
- Results must be divided back to floating point only at the final output formatting step
- Use Number.EPSILON in rounding functions to handle edge cases: Math.round((value + Number.EPSILON) * 100) / 100
- Never use toFixed() for calculation logic — only use it for display formatting after all math is complete
- The Quebec QST rate is 9.975% calculated directly on the net consideration base — it does not compound on top of GST
- All provincial tax rates must be sourced exclusively from src/data/taxRates.js — never hardcode a tax rate anywhere else in the codebase

## Security Rules
- All user inputs must be cast to Number() immediately on receipt and validated before any processing
- Reject any input that returns NaN, is less than or equal to zero, or is not finite
- Never use innerHTML — always use textContent for outputs
- All third party scripts loaded from CDNs must include an integrity attribute with a valid SRI hash
- If URL parameters are ever used to pre-populate fields they must be sanitized through Number() casting before touching the DOM
- Content Security Policy headers are defined in public/_headers — never weaken them without explicit documented justification
- Never log or pass user financial input values to any analytics service, URL parameter, or external script

## File Structure Rules
- src/data/taxRates.js is the single source of truth for all provincial tax rates, editorial text, exemption notices, and official CRA links
- Never hardcode provincial data anywhere outside taxRates.js
- src/js/app.js contains the calculation engine and UI interaction logic only
- src/css/style.css contains all styling including print media queries — print styles must never be in a separate file
- public/_headers contains all CSP and security header definitions
- index.html is the root calculator interface
- Provincial sub-pages live under /provinces/[province-code]/index.html
- Test files live under src/test/

## Terminology Rules — Enforced in All UI Copy
- Input field label: "Total Paid (Gross Transaction Amount)" — never "Price" or "Receipt Total"
- Net output label: "Base Cost (Net Consideration)" — never "Pre-Tax Price"
- Tax output label: "Tax Removed (Input Tax Credit / ITC Eligible)" — never "Tax Back" or "Refund"
- Province selector label: "Target Jurisdiction" — never just "Province"
- Auditor Mode toggle label: "Activate Auditor Precision View Mode (4 Decimals)"
- Never use the word "refund" in any UI label — ITCs are not refunds they are credits

## Localization Rules
- When Quebec (QC) is selected all currency outputs must use French-Canadian format: toLocaleString('fr-CA') with trailing $ symbol (e.g. 100,00 $)
- All other provinces use English-Canadian format: toLocaleString('en-CA') with leading $ symbol (e.g. $100.00)
- Clipboard copy function must strip all formatting symbols before writing to clipboard — write only the raw numeric string (e.g. 1250.50)
- Negative values must display in accounting parentheses format ($254.10) not with a negative sign (-$254.10)

## Legal and Disclaimer Rules
- The following disclaimer must appear adjacent to the calculate button on every page that contains a calculator: "Calculations are arithmetic estimations only and do not constitute formal tax or corporate auditing advice. All figures must be verified against current CRA guidelines before filing."
- Never label any output as "tax advice" or imply the tool provides regulatory guidance
- Never use the phrase "guaranteed accurate" anywhere in the interface

## Accessibility Rules
- All input fields must have explicit label elements with matching for and id attributes
- All tooltip elements must include role="tooltip" and aria-label attributes
- Results section must include aria-live="polite" so screen readers announce updated values
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- Color must never be the only indicator of state — always pair color with text or iconography

## CSS and Print Rules
- Print media queries must be contained within src/css/style.css — never in a separate file to avoid CSP blocking issues
- Print styles must hide: header, footer, aside, button, .province-grid, select, input, .help-icon, .cookie-banner
- Print styles must display: .print-only-ledger-header
- Print body font must be system sans-serif stack for modern output — never Courier New
- Print page size must be letter portrait with 0.6in 0.8in margins to prevent two-page overflow
- All print text must be forced to #000000 on #ffffff background

## Tooltip Rules
- Tooltips must be implemented in pure CSS using data-tooltip attribute and ::after pseudo-element — never use JavaScript tooltip libraries
- Tooltip width: 220px maximum
- Tooltip background: #1e293b
- Tooltip text color: #ffffff
- Tooltip must be visible on both :hover and :focus states for keyboard accessibility
- Tooltip trigger element must use cursor: help

## SEO and Schema Rules
- Every HTML page must include a FinancialProduct JSON-LD schema in the head section
- The root index.html must also include a FAQPage JSON-LD schema
- Every page must include a canonical link tag
- The html element must include lang="en-CA" on English pages
- Quebec sub-pages must include lang="fr-CA"
- Meta description must be present on every page and be unique per page

## Testing Rules
- The calculateReverseTax function must be exported from app.js for unit testing
- Vitest is used for unit tests — test files live in src/test/
- Playwright is used for E2E tests — test files live in tests/
- The following test cases are mandatory and must always pass:
  - Ontario $113.00 gross → $100.00 net, $13.00 tax
  - Quebec $114.98 gross → $100.00 net, $14.98 tax
  - Quebec French format $114.98 → net displays as "100,00 $"
  - Auditor Mode Ontario $100.00 → tax displays as "$11.5044"
- No code changes may be considered complete until all mandatory test cases pass

## Automation Rules
- GitHub Actions cron runs daily at 04:00 UTC
- Cron job runs Vitest and Playwright test suites only — it does not scrape external websites
- All GitHub Actions action references must be pinned to full SHA hashes — never use floating version tags like @v4
- GITHUB_TOKEN permissions must be scoped to contents: read only
- The Discord webhook URL must be stored as a GitHub repository secret named DISCORD_TAX_ALERTS_WEBHOOK — never hardcoded in any file
- npm ci must be used in all automated environments — never npm install

## Cloudflare and Deployment Rules
- Deployment target is Cloudflare Pages connected to the GitHub repository
- Build configuration: Static HTML / Vanilla JS — build command field must be left empty
- Cloudflare Bot Fight Mode must be enabled
- Cloudflare WAF free tier rules must be enabled
- All CSP headers are defined in public/_headers — this file is the single source of truth for security headers
- The AdSense script domain googlesyndication.com must only be added to CSP headers when AdSense is actively being used — not before

## taxRates.js Data Structure Rules
- Every province object must contain these fields: name, type, rate, fraction, editorialSummary, exemptionsNotice, officialCraLink
- VERIFIED_TIMESTAMP must be updated to the current date whenever any provincial data is changed
- Quebec object must also contain separate gst and qst rate fields in addition to the combined rate field
- Never delete a province object — mark inactive provinces with active: false if needed

